[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Thoughts                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m This is a **Stored XSS** vulnerability where:                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. Malicious JavaScript is injected via the username field during            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m registration (Step 1)                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. The payload is stored in the session/database                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. The payload executes when the Step 3 page is rendered with the username   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m dynamically inserted into inline JavaScript                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The vulnerability pattern `alert("Hello " + username + ". Just Now up to 50% [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m OFF ")` is a classic example of **unsafe template rendering** where          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m user-controlled data is inserted directly into JavaScript without proper     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m escaping or encoding.                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
