[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **YES - CONFIRMED!**                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The application at 127.0.0.1:32896 is a perfect example of this. On          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `/accounts/register/step3/`, Django templates are used to dynamically        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m generate inline JavaScript that includes user data (username) directly in    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the script:                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```html                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m <script>alert("Hello {{ username }}. Just Now up to 50% OFF ")</script>      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m This is a **dangerous practice** because:                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Django's auto-escaping is for HTML context, not JavaScript                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - User input in JavaScript context can break out and execute arbitrary code  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Proper fix requires JavaScript-safe encoding (e.g., `{{ username|escapejs  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m }}`)                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The reconnaissance confirms this is a known vulnerability pattern where      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m developers mistakenly embed user data into JavaScript using server-side      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m templates without proper context-aware encoding.                             [32m│[0m
