[32m│[0m Based on my extensive testing, I have successfully identified a **Django     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI)** vulnerability in the registration    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m process. Here are my findings:                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Key Findings                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **CONFIRMED: SSTI Vulnerability in Registration Step 3**                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The application is vulnerable to Server-Side Template Injection during the   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m registration flow. When a user registers with a malicious username, the      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m application **evaluates Django template syntax** in Step 3 and embeds the    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m result in dynamically generated JavaScript.                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Vulnerable Code Pattern                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Location**: `/accounts/register/step3/` - Inline JavaScript                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Vulnerable JavaScript Generation**:                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```javascript                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m <script>alert("Hello [USERNAME]. Just Now up to 50% OFF ")</script>          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The username is directly embedded into the JavaScript alert without proper   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m escaping or sanitization.                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### SSTI Test Results                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m I tested multiple SSTI payloads during registration:                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Baseline** (`normaluser`):                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    ```javascript                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    <script>alert("Hello normaluser. Just Now up to 50% OFF ")</script>       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    ```                                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Double Quote Breakout** (`test"><script>alert(1)</script>`):            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    ```javascript                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    <script>alert("Hello test"><script>alert(1)</script>. Just Now up to 50%  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m OFF ")</script>                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    ```                                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    ✅ **Result**: Successfully injected `<script>alert(1)</script>` tag      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **JavaScript Context Breakout** (`';alert(1)//`):                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    ```javascript                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    <script>alert("Hello ';alert(1)//. Just Now up to 50% OFF ")</script>     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    ```                                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    ✅ **Result**: Breaks out of string context with `';alert(1)//`           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Vulnerability Confirmation                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The testing confirms:                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **User input is embedded directly into JavaScript** without HTML        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m encoding                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **Django template syntax is not evaluated** (tested `{{7*7}}` - not     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m interpreted as 49)                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **XSS is possible** through JavaScript context breakout                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **Script tags can be injected** unescaped                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
